title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
Hi, hope you guys are doing great.

820-2850 not turning on, green light on charger, no visible liquid damage. PPBUS_G3H,  PP5V_S5,  PP3V3_S5  are prensent but  PP5V_S5  is missing.  PP5V_S5  pulses to about 2.5v for a fraction of a second.

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
"PP5V_S5 ...  prensent but  PP5V_S5  is missing"
Can you clarify your post???

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
If 5V_S3 pulses, then check for pulse at other coils.
Try starting in SMC bypass mode also.

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
All coils pulse except for C1689 and C1690. 

With SMC bypass the fans only spin for a sec.

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
These caps are associated with 1V05_S0, which comes from one of the coils you've said pulsing!
Maybe not all pulsing; what about VCORE?
Can you catch a pulse at ALL_SYS_PWRGD?

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
Sorry, i meant L7030, not those caps. L7030 not pulsing. 

PPVCORE_S0_CPU pulsing.

PP3V3_S0GPU pulsing.

ALL_SYS_PWRGD pulsing.

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
L7030 should have stable voltage, no pulse of course.

Change C9560, just in case.

Any pulse at PLT_RESET_L?

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
Replaced C9560, still nothing.

No pulse at  PLT_RESET_L

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
So PCH doesn't know if power on sequence is acomplished.
Check for pulse at CPU_PWRGD, PM_MEM_PWRGD and CPUVTTS0_PGOOD.

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
CPU_PWRGD pulsing

 PM_MEM_PWRGD pulsing

CPUVTTS0_PGOOD pulsing

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message:
RIP...

Thank you so much. Have a good day.

title: 820-2850 no PP5V_S3
message: Replaced U6100 with known working from another board of the same model but still no fan spin. Thank you very much for all of your help.
